      "content": "That makes sense. Overloading the operators seems doable. Since I'm on a very limited hardware target, I don't have the luxury of running Valgrind or a heavy profiler. \n\nIf I implement a custom wrapper/sentry for `new` and `delete` to track the address and a timestamp, how should I handle the storage for that metadata without causing more fragmentation or consuming the very RAM I'm trying to save? Also, how would you recommend I structure the search once I have a list of un-freed pointers?",
